SIMPLE: islam
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Islam
<hw>Is"lam</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>isl⟦amac⟧m</ets> obedience to the will of God, submission, humbling
one's self, resigning one's self to the divine disposal. Cf.
<er>Moslem</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The religion of the Muslims; Islamism. Their formula
of faith is: There is no God but Allah, and Mohammed is his prophet. An
older term is <altname>Mohammedanism</altname>, but this term is
considered offensive by many Muslims, as their submission is to Allah,
not Mohammed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The whole body of Muslims, or the countries which
they occupy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Islamabad</ent>⟦br⟧
